headline: Which High-Yield Dividend Stock Is Cheaper: Stanley Black & Decker or Constellation Brands?
summary: Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE: SWK) and Constellation Brands (NYSE: STZ) have dividend yields as I write this of around 4% and 2.3%, respectively.  Between Stanley Black & Decker and Constellation Brands, which is the better buy?  Shares of Stanley Black & Decker cost much less than Constellation Brands shares, but that doesn't tell you which stock is the better value.
